parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure of Auto High Beam Function
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the auto high beam function can lead to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: The high beams do not activate when the headlights are in the "Auto" position
the high beams only work when the lights are in the "ON" position
the high beams can only be activated by switching to manual mode
the paddle or switch does not activate the high beams in auto mode.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The hybrid system malfunction can cause the engine to shut off while driving, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially on highways or city streets.
symptoms: The engine shuts off automatically while driving
the vehicle hesitates when the gas engine is communicating with the electric battery
the vehicle acts like it is in neutral for about 5 seconds
the vehicle will not accelerate past a certain speed (e.g.
29 mph)
the "D" indicator on the shifter knob and driver info panel screen blinks
numerous error messages and icons are displayed
including the check engine light
battery warning light
check hybrid electrical system light and warning
and service electronic stability control warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system failure can cause various malfunctions, including the loss of power, brake pedal kicking back, and gear shifter moving when the vehicle is dead, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power
the odometer blinks
blind spot indicators stay illuminated
the rear back-up camera displays a "system unavailable" fault
the brake pedal kicks back when trying to start the vehicle
the gear shifter moves when the vehicle is dead.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden shutdown of the engine while driving can cause loss of control, increasing the risk of accidents, and potentially leaving the driver stranded. The inability to shift gears or restart the engine can further exacerbate the situation.
symptoms: The engine shuts off while driving
the vehicle shifts into park or neutral unexpectedly
the vehicle is unable to accelerate past a certain speed
the "D" indicator on the shifter and driver information panel blinks
error codes are displayed on the diagnostic system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning infotainment system can distract the driver, leading to accidents, and may also prevent the vehicle from shutting off properly, causing safety concerns.
symptoms: The infotainment system remains on despite the engine shutting off
the system displays incorrect or misleading information
the system fails to respond to user input.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission control system can cause the vehicle to become stuck in a particular gear, leading to loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle is unable to shift gears
the "D" indicator on the shifter and driver information panel blinks
the vehicle is unable to accelerate past a certain speed.
